# selfsuvis project rules

- Never create a git commit unless the user explicitly asks for one.
- Never add `from __future__ import annotations`.
- Keep project scripts flat under `scripts/`; do not introduce new script subdirectories.
- Top-level `scripts/` should be shell entrypoints only. Put Python implementations under `src/selfsuvis/...` and call them from shell wrappers when needed.
- Reuse `scripts/common.sh` for shared shell behavior instead of duplicating root/env/bootstrap logic.

# repo map

- Main Python source: `src/selfsuvis/`
- Coop / IoT integration: `src/selfsuvis/coop_pilot/`
- Docker configs: `docker/`
- Docs: `docs/`
- Project shell entrypoints: `scripts/`

# practical commands

- Prefer `make venv`, `make test-unit`, `make lint`, `make up`, `make down`, `make logs`.
- PostgreSQL migration: `python -m selfsuvis.scripts.migrate_postgres`
- Qdrant reset: `scripts/reset_qdrant.sh`
- Coop stack entrypoints use flat paths: `scripts/bootstrap.sh`, `scripts/compose.sh`, `scripts/gen-env.sh`, `scripts/ensure_data_dirs.sh`.

# architecture shorthand

- API: `src/selfsuvis/app/`
- Worker: `src/selfsuvis/worker/`
- UI: `src/selfsuvis/ui/`
- Local/LangGraph pipeline: `src/selfsuvis/pipeline/workflows/local/`
- Mapping: `src/selfsuvis/pipeline/mapping/`
- Fusion: `src/selfsuvis/pipeline/fusion/`
- Training/adaptation: `src/selfsuvis/pipeline/training/`

# config reminders

- Runtime settings live in `src/selfsuvis/pipeline/core/config.py`.
- Python target is 3.10+.
